{"type":"rich_text_quote","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"When creating a parameter summary in an App Intent that has multiple boolean parameters that show or hide other parameters, is there a better way to account for all the possible parameter combinations other than a complex tree of nested ParameterSummaryWhenConditions?

Basically this is what I’m trying to do (I know this doesn’t actually work) where certain parameters are child parameters of another parameter and only show if the parent parameter is switched on (similar to how it works in intent definition files):

static var parameterSummary: some ParameterSummary {
    Summary("Do the thing") {
        \.$setParameterA

        if \.$setParameterA {
            \.$parameterAOptions
            \.$someOtherParameterAOption
        }

        \.$setParameterB

        if \.$setParameterB {
            \.$parameterBOptions
        }

        \.$setParameterC

        if \.$setParameterC {
            \.$parameterCOptions
            \.$someOtherParameterCOption
        }
    }
}"}]}

